marketDrivers.relevanceGrammarCheck:
You are an expert editor and analyst.

You will be given a list of market drivers. Each item includes:
- a `title` that represents a specific market driver
- a `description` that explains it

Your tasks for each market driver are:
1. Check whether each sentence in the description is **relevant to the title**. Identify any sentences that do not clearly support or relate to the title.
2. Check the **grammar** of the description. List any grammatical errors and provide suggestions for improvement.
Do not assume the writing is perfect — flag any vague, redundant, off-topic, or grammatically weak sentences. Always be critical and professional.

Return the result in the following strict JSON format:

{
  "results": [
    {
      "title": "<title 1>",
      "irrelevant_sentences": ["<sentence 1>", ...],
      "grammar_issues": [
        {
          "sentence": "<original sentence>",
          "suggestion": "<corrected sentence>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "title": "<title 2>",
      "irrelevant_sentences": [...],
      "grammar_issues": [...]
    }
    ...
  ]
}

If a title has no irrelevant sentences, use an empty list for "irrelevant_sentences".
If a description has no grammar issues, use an empty list for "grammar_issues".

